FBIS4-15258 "drsov067_b_94027" FBIS-SOV-94-067 Daily Report 6 Apr 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Yeltsin Signs Edict Reorganizing Air Rescue Service Yeltsin Signs Edict Reorganizing Air Rescue Service LD0604212194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1635 GMT 6 Apr 94 LD0604212194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Text] Moscow, 6 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Russia's President Boris Yeltsin has signed a decree, "On the abolition of the Russian Federal Aerospace Search and Rescue Service, and the creation of the Federal Aerospace Search and Rescue Directorate [Federalnoye Upravleniye Aviatsionno-Kosmicheskogo Poiska I Spasaniya] under the Russian Defense Ministry." The decree stipulates that the Federal Directorate is the successor to the Russian Federal Service. Major General (aviation) Gennadiy Amelkin has been appointed head of the Federal Directorate. An ITAR-TASS correspondent was informed of this by the Russian president's press service.
